<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Tern Setup Guide — Adventure the World Travels</title>
<style>
  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display:ital@0;1&family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap');

  :root {
    --navy:       #2B3A52;
    --teal:       #0F6E56;
    --teal-mid:   #1D9E75;
    --teal-light: #D6F0E8;
    --sky:        #E8F4FA;
    --gold:       #C8A84B;
    --gold-light: #F5EDD5;
    --orange:     #C45E0A;
    --orange-lt:  #FDF0E6;
    --red:        #8B1A1A;
    --red-lt:     #F8E8E8;
    --gray:       #7A7A7A;
    --gray-lt:    #F6F8FA;
    --border:     #E2E8F0;
    --white:      #FFFFFF;
    --text:       #1A2433;
  }

  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  body {
    font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    background: #F0F4F8;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ── NAV ── */
  nav {
    background: var(--navy);
    padding: 0 2rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0;
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 100;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,.25);
  }
  .nav-brand {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    color: var(--gold);
    font-size: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem 1rem 0;
    border-right: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.15);
    margin-right: 0.5rem;
    white-space: nowrap;
    letter-spacing: .02em;
  }
  nav a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,.75);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: .78rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 1rem .85rem;
    transition: color .15s, background .15s;
    letter-spacing: .03em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  nav a:hover, nav a.active { color: #fff; background: rgba(255,255,255,.08); }

  /* ── HERO ── */
  .hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--navy) 0%, #1A3A4A 60%, var(--teal) 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 3.5rem 2rem 3rem;
    text-align: center;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute; inset: 0;
    background: url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg width='60' height='60' viewBox='0 0 60 60' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cg fill='none' fill-rule='evenodd'%3E%3Cg fill='%23ffffff' fill-opacity='0.03'%3E%3Ccircle cx='30' cy='30' r='20'/%3E%3C/g%3E%3C/g%3E%3C/svg%3E");
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .hero-eyebrow {
    font-size: .72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: .14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin-bottom: .75rem;
  }
  .hero h1 {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 4vw, 2.8rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: .75rem;
  }
  .hero p {
    font-size: .95rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,.78);
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto 1.75rem;
  }
  .hero-chips {
    display: flex; gap: .5rem; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center;
  }
  .chip {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.12);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2);
    color: rgba(255,255,255,.9);
    border-radius: 99px;
    padding: .3rem .85rem;
    font-size: .75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  /* ── LAYOUT ── */
  .container { max-width: 960px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 1.5rem; }

  /* ── SECTIONS ── */
  .section {
    background: var(--white);
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin: 1.5rem auto;
    max-width: 960px;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,.07);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .section-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: .85rem;
    padding: 1.1rem 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    cursor: pointer;
    user-select: none;
  }
  .section-header:hover { background: var(--gray-lt); }
  .section-icon {
    width: 34px; height: 34px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    font-size: 1rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .section-header h2 {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--navy);
    flex: 1;
  }
  .section-header .badge {
    font-size: .68rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: .2rem .6rem;
    border-radius: 99px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: .06em;
  }
  .badge-action  { background: var(--orange-lt); color: var(--orange); }
  .badge-review  { background: var(--gold-light); color: #7A5A00; }
  .badge-info    { background: var(--teal-light); color: var(--teal); }
  .chevron { color: var(--gray); font-size: .9rem; transition: transform .2s; }
  .chevron.open { transform: rotate(180deg); }

  .section-body { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; display: none; }
  .section-body.open { display: block; }

  /* ── CONTENT BLOCKS ── */
  .lead {
    font-size: .9rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--border);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: .82rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: .08em;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin: 1.25rem 0 .6rem;
  }
  h3:first-child { margin-top: 0; }

  /* ── STATUS CHIPS ── */
  .status-flow {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: .4rem;
    margin: .75rem 0 1rem;
  }
  .status {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: .35rem;
    padding: .35rem .85rem;
    border-radius: 99px;
    font-size: .78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: .02em;
  }
  .status-arrow { color: var(--gray); font-size: .8rem; font-weight: 400; }
  .s-new       { background: #E8F4FA; color: #1A6B8A; border: 1.5px solid #BDE0F0; }
  .s-planning  { background: #EDE8F8; color: #5B4A8A; border: 1.5px solid #C9BEF0; }
  .s-proposal  { background: var(--gold-light); color: var(--orange); border: 1.5px solid #E8C87A; }
  .s-booked    { background: var(--teal-light); color: var(--teal); border: 1.5px solid var(--teal-mid); }
  .s-pretravel { background: #E8F0FA; color: var(--navy); border: 1.5px solid #B8CCE8; }
  .s-traveling { background: #FDF0E6; color: var(--orange); border: 1.5px solid #F0C8A0; }
  .s-home      { background: #D6F0E8; color: var(--teal); border: 1.5px solid var(--teal-mid); }
  .s-ghost     { background: #F8E8E8; color: var(--red); border: 1.5px solid #E8B8B8; }
  .s-cancel    { background: #f0f0f0; color: #666; border: 1.5px solid #ccc; }
  .s-archive   { background: #f0f0f0; color: #555; border: 1.5px solid #bbb; }

  /* ── CARDS GRID ── */
  .card-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: .85rem;
    margin: .75rem 0;
  }
  .card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: var(--gray-lt);
  }
  .card-label {
    font-size: .7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: .09em;
    color: var(--gray);
    margin-bottom: .4rem;
  }
  .card p { font-size: .83rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.55; }

  /* ── ALERT BOXES ── */
  .alert {
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: .85rem 1rem;
    font-size: .83rem;
    margin: .75rem 0;
    display: flex;
    gap: .65rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .alert-icon { font-size: 1rem; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: .05rem; }
  .alert-action  { background: var(--orange-lt); border-left: 3px solid var(--orange); color: #6B3000; }
  .alert-info    { background: var(--sky); border-left: 3px solid #1A6B8A; color: #1A3A52; }
  .alert-tip     { background: var(--teal-light); border-left: 3px solid var(--teal-mid); color: var(--teal); }
  .alert-warn    { background: var(--red-lt); border-left: 3px solid var(--red); color: var(--red); }

  /* ── QUESTION BLOCKS ── */
  .question-list { list-style: none; margin: .75rem 0; }
  .question-list li {
    display: flex;
    gap: .65rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: .6rem .75rem;
    border-radius: 7px;
    font-size: .84rem;
    margin-bottom: .35rem;
    background: var(--gray-lt);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .q-icon { font-size: .95rem; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .q-text { color: var(--navy); }
  .q-sub  { font-size: .75rem; color: var(--gray); display: block; margin-top: .15rem; }

  /* ── WORKFLOW STEPS ── */
  .workflow-steps { margin: .75rem 0; }
  .wf-step {
    display: flex;
    gap: .85rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-bottom: .6rem;
  }
  .wf-num {
    width: 26px; height: 26px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--teal);
    color: white;
    font-size: .72rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: .1rem;
  }
  .wf-content h4 { font-size: .84rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--navy); margin-bottom: .15rem; }
  .wf-content p  { font-size: .8rem; color: var(--gray); line-height: 1.5; }

  /* ── TAG TABLE ── */
  .tag-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: .82rem; margin: .75rem 0; }
  .tag-table th {
    background: var(--navy);
    color: white;
    padding: .5rem .75rem;
    text-align: left;
    font-size: .72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: .05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .tag-table td { padding: .55rem .75rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); vertical-align: top; }
  .tag-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray-lt); }
  .tag-pill {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--sky);
    border: 1px solid #BDE0F0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    padding: .15rem .5rem;
    font-size: .72rem;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    color: #1A6B8A;
  }

  /* ── DIVIDER ── */
  .divider { border: none; border-top: 1px dashed var(--border); margin: 1.1rem 0; }

  /* ── PAGE FOOTER ── */
  footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2rem;
    font-size: .78rem;
    color: var(--gray);
  }

  /* ── EXPAND ALL ── */
  .toolbar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    max-width: 960px;
    margin: 1.25rem auto .25rem;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .toolbar-title { font-size: .8rem; color: var(--gray); font-weight: 500; }
  .btn-sm {
    background: var(--navy);
    color: white;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: .4rem .9rem;
    font-size: .75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background .15s;
  }
  .btn-sm:hover { background: var(--teal); }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    nav a { display: none; }
    .hero { padding: 2.5rem 1.25rem 2rem; }
    .section-body { padding: 1rem; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- NAV -->
<nav>
  <div class="nav-brand">Tern Guide ✈</div>
  <a href="#statuses" class="active">Statuses</a>
  <a href="#settings">Settings</a>
  <a href="#library">Library</a>
  <a href="#forms">Forms</a>
  <a href="#emails">Emails</a>
  <a href="#workflows">Workflows</a>
</nav>

<!-- HERO -->
<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-eyebrow">Adventure the World Travels · Tern Setup Guide</div>
  <h1>Your Tern Cheat Sheet,<br><em>Christine</em></h1>
  <p>A step-by-step guide to getting your Tern setup streamlined, consistent, and ready to work for you — so no client falls through the cracks.</p>
  <div class="hero-chips">
    <span class="chip">🗂 Trip Statuses</span>
    <span class="chip">⚙️ Business Settings</span>
    <span class="chip">📚 Library</span>
    <span class="chip">📋 Forms</span>
    <span class="chip">✉️ Email Templates</span>
    <span class="chip">⚡ Workflows</span>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="toolbar">
  <span class="toolbar-title">Click any section to expand</span>
  <button class="btn-sm" onclick="toggleAll()">Expand All</button>
</div>

<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────
     SECTION 1 — TRIP STATUSES
───────────────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="section" id="statuses">
  <div class="section-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
    <div class="section-icon" style="background:#E8F4FA;">🗂</div>
    <h2>Trip Statuses</h2>
    <span class="badge badge-action">Action Required</span>
    <span class="chevron">▼</span>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <p class="lead">Your current status list has grown too long and includes statuses that overlap or don't serve a clear purpose. Here's a recommended streamlined flow — and some questions for you about a few of them.</p>

    <h3>✅ Recommended Status Flow</h3>
    <div class="status-flow">
      <span class="status s-new">🌱 New Lead</span>
      <span class="status-arrow">→</span>
      <span class="status s-planning">🗺 Planning</span>
      <span class="status-arrow">→</span>
      <span class="status s-proposal">📄 Proposal Sent</span>
      <span class="status-arrow">→</span>
      <span class="status s-booked">✅ Booked</span>
      <span class="status-arrow">→</span>
      <span class="status s-pretravel">🗓 Pre-Travel</span>
      <span class="status-arrow">→</span>
      <span class="status s-traveling">✈️ Traveling</span>
      <span class="status-arrow">→</span>
      <span class="status s-home">🏡 Welcome Home</span>
    </div>
    <div class="status-flow">
      <span class="status s-ghost">👻 Ghosted</span>
      <span class="status s-cancel">✕ Cancelled</span>
      <span class="status s-archive">📦 Archived</span>
    </div>

    <div class="alert alert-info">
      <span class="alert-icon">ℹ️</span>
      <div><strong>Pre-Travel</strong> triggers automatically at 30 days out from the trip start date. This is when the pre-travel document wrap-up task fires and the final detail emails go out.</div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">
    <h3>📝 Notes on Specific Statuses</h3>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-label">Booked</div>
        <p>This means the <strong>deposit has been paid</strong> and the trip is secured — but there may still be elements to plan (excursions, transfers, hotels, etc.). Booked ≠ fully planned.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-label">Post-Travel → Removed</div>
        <p><strong>Post-Travel</strong> and <strong>Welcome Home</strong> have been merged into a single <strong>Welcome Home</strong> status. No need for two statuses at this stage.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-label">Ghosted</div>
        <p>Keep this as a <strong>tag</strong> rather than a status if you want to be able to filter — or use it as a status to clearly mark leads that went quiet. Either works.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-label">Intake → Removed</div>
        <p><strong>Intake</strong> and <strong>Sent Planning</strong> don't map to a clear stage in the client journey. <strong>New Lead</strong> covers everything from first contact through your initial call.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">
    <h3>❓ Questions for You, Christine</h3>
    <ul class="question-list">
      <li><span class="q-icon">💬</span><span class="q-text"><strong>Groups, Prospect Trips, Dream Ideas</strong> — what was your intention for these? Are they types of trips, pipeline categories, or something else? <span class="q-sub">Knowing the purpose helps determine whether these should be statuses, tags, or trip types.</span></span></li>
      <li><span class="q-icon">💬</span><span class="q-text"><strong>Traveled vs. Stored</strong> — what does "Stored" mean to you? Is this different from Archived? <span class="q-sub">If "Traveled" = trips that are complete, this maps to Welcome Home. "Stored" may simply be Archived.</span></span></li>
      <li><span class="q-icon">💬</span><span class="q-text"><strong>Archived vs. Cancelled</strong> — do you need both, or would a single "Inactive" category cover all trips that are no longer active? <span class="q-sub">Simpler is usually better here.</span></span></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────
     SECTION 2 — BUSINESS SETTINGS
───────────────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="section" id="settings">
  <div class="section-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
    <div class="section-icon" style="background:#FDF0E6;">⚙️</div>
    <h2>Business Settings</h2>
    <span class="badge badge-review">Review Needed</span>
    <span class="chevron">▼</span>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <p class="lead">Several settings need to be confirmed or cleaned up. Work through each item below and confirm your preference so we can finalize your setup.</p>

    <h3>📅 Scheduling — Planning Consultation Link</h3>
    <div class="alert alert-info">
      <span class="alert-icon">✅</span>
      <div>Confirm: <strong>Can the "Planning Consultation with Christine" link be used as your client-facing booking tool?</strong> If yes, this link will be embedded in your initial inquiry email and onboarding templates so clients can self-schedule directly.</div>
    </div>

    <h3>💳 Planning Fees — Stripe</h3>
    <div class="alert alert-tip">
      <span class="alert-icon">✅</span>
      <div>Confirm: <strong>All planning fees will be sent via Stripe.</strong> Your email template (Next Steps + Trip Recap) includes language for both the Stripe invoice and agency agreement. If this is correct, no changes needed.</div>
    </div>

    <h3>❓ Items to Clarify</h3>
    <ul class="question-list">
      <li><span class="q-icon">❓</span><span class="q-text"><strong>Project Expedition</strong> — what is this, and does it belong in your Tern setup? <span class="q-sub">Please clarify so we know whether to keep, integrate, or remove it.</span></span></li>
      <li><span class="q-icon">❓</span><span class="q-text"><strong>Travel Insurance</strong> — are you currently presenting insurance through a specific provider in Tern? <span class="q-sub">We want to confirm the right touchpoint in your workflow for sending insurance options.</span></span></li>
    </ul>

    <hr class="divider">
    <h3>🏷 Disney Cruise Line Tags — Simplify</h3>
    <div class="alert alert-action">
      <span class="alert-icon">⚠️</span>
      <div>You currently have a tag for <strong>each individual Disney Cruise Line ship</strong>. This is more granular than necessary and creates clutter. <strong>Recommendation: consolidate to a single "Disney Cruise Line" tag</strong>, or at most separate by category (Disney Cruise vs. Disney World). Confirm whether ship-level tags are truly useful to you before keeping them.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────
     SECTION 3 — LIBRARY
───────────────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="section" id="library">
  <div class="section-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
    <div class="section-icon" style="background:#D6F0E8;">📚</div>
    <h2>Library</h2>
    <span class="badge badge-action">Build Out</span>
    <span class="chevron">▼</span>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <p class="lead">You currently have only 25 activity items in your library. This is an area with a big opportunity to save time — but the goal isn't to build from scratch. Start with what you already know.</p>

    <div class="alert alert-tip">
      <span class="alert-icon">💡</span>
      <div><strong>Best approach:</strong> Go through your existing active and recently traveled trips and pull the hotels, excursions, and transfers you book repeatedly. Save those to the library first. Building from real trips is faster and more useful than creating items speculatively.</div>
    </div>

    <h3>Where to Start</h3>
    <div class="workflow-steps">
      <div class="wf-step">
        <div class="wf-num">1</div>
        <div class="wf-content">
          <h4>Review active & recently traveled trips</h4>
          <p>Look at trips currently in Traveling, Pre-Travel, or Welcome Home status. Pull any hotels, transfers, or experiences you plan to book again.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="wf-step">
        <div class="wf-num">2</div>
        <div class="wf-content">
          <h4>Save frequently used hotels first</h4>
          <p>Hotels you book for Disney, cruises, or FIT trips should be saved to the library with your standard descriptions already personalized in your voice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="wf-step">
        <div class="wf-num">3</div>
        <div class="wf-content">
          <h4>Build itinerary templates from real trips</h4>
          <p>Once you have library items saved, you can assemble them into reusable itinerary templates by destination — so new trips of the same type can be built in minutes, not hours.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="wf-step">
        <div class="wf-num">4</div>
        <div class="wf-content">
          <h4>Add activities, excursions & transfers</h4>
          <p>Shore excursions, airport transfers, and common day-trip options can all be library items. Add as you encounter them, not all at once.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────
     SECTION 4 — FORMS
───────────────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="section" id="forms">
  <div class="section-header" onclick="toggle(this)">
    <div class="section-icon" style="background:#EDE8F8;">📋</div>
    <h2>Forms</h2>
    <span class="badge badge-info">In Progress</span>
    <span class="chevron">▼</span>
  </div>
  <div class="section-body">
    <p class="lead">Forms are where your client process begins. The initial trip inquiry form is your entry point into Tern — here's how it's designed to work.</p>

    <h3>How the Trip Inquiry Form Works</h3>
    <div class="workflow-steps">
